ical input sequence that we want to process. The nonlinear crystal from the cavity applies a quadratic Hamiltonian, that we can write in a generic way as [EQUATION] with coupling parameters \\alpha_{ij} and \\beta_{ij} . If any of the \\beta_{ij} terms are different from zero, the crystal generates squeezing and this increases the squeezing present in the circulating reservoir pulse. With this setup, the response of the quantum observables to the classical input fed by the input squeezing phase, \\phi_{k} from Eq. ( 2 ), becomes nonlinear, as can be seen in Fig. 2 (b).", "equation": "\\hat{H}_{\\chi^{(2)}}=\\sum_{i,j=1}^{N}\\left(\\alpha_{ij}\\hat{a}_{i}^{\\dagger}\\hat{a}_{j}+\\beta_{ij}\\hat{a}_{i}^{\\dagger}\\hat{a}_{j}^{\\dagger}+\\text{h.c.}\\right),\\quad\\left(i\\geq j\\right)", "has_answer": true, "start": 683, "end": 704}
